This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on face detection, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV. The paper also proposes a novel framework that utilizes metric learning and graph cut techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), respectively. Therefore, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The paper also presents experimental results, which involve comparing the proposed method with state-of-the-art methods, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.MM (multimedia). Finally, since the paper deals with face detection, which is a security-related application, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (cryptography and security).
